      "writtenOn": "2020-08-28T14:00:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wrote this originally, but now mostly use a kdevelop plugin for gn I wrote (which is really fast, like can load up the Chromium project in about half a second). There are a few other people on our team who use it (mostly with CLion) and we do test that Skia builds with it.\n\nNote that Chromium has a copy of this that I think they use with gradle somehow [0] and they also did something very similar [1]. I think what they did there is a bit better since that caches the results directly instead of trying to figure out how to reduce the calculation. Also, I suspect the code here at PS1 is dropping (transitive) dependencies since it is just skipping things and not additionally adding cached results to object_dependencies. Of course their change only applies to objects, but this could also be done to libraries.\n\n[0] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/master:build/android/gradle/gn_to_cmake.py\n[1] https://codereview.chromium.org/2866863003/diff/1/build/android/gradle/gn_to_cmake.py",
